Package: E3AtlasDuckplyr
Type: Package
Title: Duckplyr Expression Atlas Import Utilities for E3 Ligase Resources
Version: 0.3.7
Authors@R: c(
    person(given = "Pete", family = "Thorpe", role = c("aut", "cre"), email = "p.thorpe@example.org")
    )
Description: Utilities for building an incremental Expression Atlas import layer
    for an E3 ligase and HOG database. The package keeps a simple species file,
    discovers Expression Atlas experiments, checks remote files before download,
    keeps experiments with downloadable TPM/FPKM matrices by default, downloads
    only missing non-empty files, normalises expression matrices into long
    Parquet datasets using a Python streaming importer by default, imports
    SDRF/condensed-SDRF sample metadata into separate Parquet datasets, and
    exposes lazy query helpers through duckplyr. Version 0.3.7 keeps the v0.3.6 condensed-SDRF group parsing and fixes the
    pyarrow unit-test path reader so hive-style partition folders do not create
    duplicate partition columns when a single Parquet file is read directly.
